Write a function which returns the sort index of a given string. The
sort index should represent the zero-based position of the string in
an alphabetically ascending sorted array of all possible strings
composed of the same letters and the same length of the input string.
Assume input ASCII letters a-z and a max input length of 20.

Example:

run => 15

0  nnn
1  nnr
2  nnu
3  nrn
4  nrr
5  nru
6  nun
7  nur
8  nuu
9  rnn
10 rnr
11 rnu
12 rrn
13 rrr
14 rru
15 run
16 rur
17 ruu
18 unn
19 unr
20 unu
21 urn
22 urr
23 uru
24 uun
25 uur
26 uuu